ant hoopla on the part of many individuals that &quot;FGs shouldn't be reservable,&quot; I wish to know how we can bring this matter back to vote and settle it again so this (currently very lame argument) either goes away or reaches its culmination.<br>
<br>
The argument I've heard &quot;but they shouldn't be&quot; seems grossly inadequate given that currently they ARE, and the other argument &quot;we didn't think we were poaching&quot; wears thin when it happens twice in a week.  Either way, let's settle it.<br>
<br>
Proposal:<br>
Remove Sol B Fire Giants from the reservation list.<br>
<br>
Discussion:<br>
Personally I disagree with my own motion <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   but it is more important to me that we get it on the table to discuss and resolve than that my particular view win.  Here's what I can see as pro's and con's:<br>
IN SUPPORT OF THE MOTION:<br>
 - Folks are ever more inclined to ignore the reservation board, at least with respect to FGs.  Recognize an accomplished act of piracy.  Yes I know that's morally slimy people, please don't flame me for expressing it.  Fact is it's been done unto me this week, and I've already seen many folks argue much the same thing even among the victims.  I'm just giving voice to it here.<br>
 - They require little or no more than a group to do.  One does not want to reserve sub-raid-level mobs.<br>
 - They are &quot;relatively&quot; fast spawners.<br>
 - The loot is mostly high-priced &quot;trash&quot; with a couple of good items (Tranix crown, e.g.) rarely dropped.<br>
 - It's one less thing for the mods to deal with.  Do not underestimate that as a real virtue.<br>
<br>
OPPOSING THE MOTION:<br>
 - Given the difference between European time and US time, if the European guilds or groups decided to camp them as targets-in-themselves or for Ragefire for several days straight, we in the US would not see the FGs for that time.  The US groups could have a similar impact on Pacific-based players, though I think that's less as the time differences now exceed FG spawn time.<br>
 - They remain surpassing good exercise/experience for up and coming raiders, of comparable level, difficulty and geography as Nagafen (and to a slightly lesser degree only, of Vox).  IF you accept FGs as a &quot;training raid&quot; then asking would-be raid leaders to accept a burden of learning their craft while trying to fit around other raids in progress is asking too much.<br>
 - That they CAN be taken out by a single group does not mean they are/must be.  If you don't have a 'chanter along, you need superior healing or firepower or tanking to make up the defiency.  A single group of 60s could dominate much of &quot;old&quot; hate at least and make a nice dent on the second floor, but I do not see anyone moving to make Hate unreservable.  That's because a substantial amount of the population still has need for the old system.  The &quot;one group can do it&quot; argument in effect says if you aren't in your high 40s or above, you don't do FGs - and that is NOT how a lot of the old school raiders did it.<br>
<br>
OK.   sigh, flame away.<br>
<br>
Hadron Soulbrightener<br>
Minstrel<br>
Officer (ret) A Higher Order<br>
