<br>
I am troubled however, that people rant with such venom and mean spirited feelings when there is conflict around FGs.  Frankly, if a raid gets underminded as in the recent probelm with Orri and Enshadowed, it should be worked out in game.  Truely dishonorable acts and treachory I do like seeing ranted about, but communication break downs or mistakes give us all the impression that we cannot get a long, and frankly this is not the case.  Many, many guilds try very hard to work things out on Brell, it is only when a small number fail that we get rants, or when an individual with too much passion gets a bit too worked up.<br>
<br>
I belive FGs shoud remain reservalble, for this reason.  NOT as a training ground for raiding, but rather a training ground for problem solving/conflict resolution.  FGs are an excelllent place for peole to learn how to share, not how to plan a raid.  They learn to communicate with other guilds, and how to make things work, and when they coomunicate badly and come ranting to the boards, they get a chance for the brell community to say, for example, hey Orri, relax, this can be worked out and everyone can win, instead of someone being &quot;punished&quot; for trying to play the game.  Iremember killing FGs and getting a tell from the good Knight Thorndar, asking when we would be done so he could come with his crew and kill ragefire.  We coordianted it, he came after we were done and I belive was succesful.  No problems, no conflict, 2 happy raiding partners.  I beleive the majority of guilds on Brell act this way<br>
<br>
FGs serve this purpose, and for the good of the community, I think they need to be kept reservable.<br>
<br>
Eoral Solis<br>
